•   { inv.(n,z,y) ∧ a.n < 0 } y:= E { y = f.(n+1) }

(1) E = ? // E = (y - 1) ↑ 0

≡   Hoare triple

    inv.(n,z,y) ∧ a.n ≥ 0 ⇒ wp.(y:= E).(y = f.(n+1))

≡   Prove ⇒

    •   wp.(y:= E).(y = f.(n+1))

    (2) 0 ≤ n ≤ #a
    
    (3) z = m.n
    
    (4) y = f.n

    (5) n ≠ #a
    
    (6) a.n ≥ 0

    ≡   Assignment
    
        E = f.(n+1)

    ≡   Theory [12], using assumption (6)

        E = (f.n - 1) ↑ 0

    ≡   Assumption (4)

        E = (y - 1) ↑ 0

    ■

⋯   true

■